<title>FRANCE: RISK OF FURTHER STORMS IN NORTH, EAST FRANCE.</title>
<headline>RISK OF FURTHER STORMS IN NORTH, EAST FRANCE.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Most of France will bask in hot weather on Wednesday but bad weather could again get in the way of the grain harvest in the northeast, the Meteo France weather service said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The bureau forecast showers in northern Picardie, Ile de France surrounding Paris, and Champagne-Ardennes in the east.</p>
<p>Thunderstorms were not excluded, it said.</p>
<p>Farmers are racing to finish the harvest in parts of those areas after delays caused by storms and heavy rain last week.</p>
<p>Meteo France predicted average temperatures of 30 degrees Celsius near Paris, 29 degrees in the town of Lille, which is just to the north of Picardie, and 31 degrees in the east.</p>
<p>Average temperatures in southern France would be 30 degrees everywhere.</p>
